<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,303,267,293]" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,267,293]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,313,446]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName authority="Haran &amp; Hansen &amp; Benoit &amp; Cbgp, 2020" authorityName="Haran &amp; Hansen &amp; Benoit &amp; Cbgp" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,436,313,339]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Phlyctinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aloevorus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,436,313,339]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Phlyctinus aloevorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[444,535,314,340]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authority="Haran &amp; Hansen &amp; Benoit &amp; Cbgp, 2020" authorityName="Haran &amp; Hansen &amp; Benoit &amp; Cbgp" authorityYear="2020" box="[715,845,313,339]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Phlyctinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littoralis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[715,845,313,339]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">P. littoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[853,944,314,340]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
species group, in which it is closest to 
<taxonomicName authority="Haran &amp; Hansen &amp; Benoit &amp; Cbgp, 2020" authorityName="Haran &amp; Hansen &amp; Benoit &amp; Cbgp" authorityYear="2020" box="[189,355,349,375]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Phlyctinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="planithorax" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,355,349,375]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">P. planithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[362,453,349,375]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(see discussion under that species for distinguishing characters). It can easily be distinguished from specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Haran &amp; Hansen &amp; Benoit &amp; Cbgp, 2020" authorityName="Haran &amp; Hansen &amp; Benoit &amp; Cbgp" authorityYear="2020" box="[579,710,384,410]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Phlyctinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="littoralis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[579,710,384,410]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">P. littoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[717,808,384,410]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the presence of a distinct median carina on the prothorax. Both species show an uncorrected p-distance of 5.3%.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
